247
00:15:26.487 --> 00:15:28.091
You can't keep going out
like this.

248
00:15:28.193 --> 00:15:30.063
We thought it was gonna be
one time.

249
00:15:30.165 --> 00:15:32.324
If he wants to see you again.
we have to meet him.

250
00:15:32.426 --> 00:15:33.861
She finish all her schoolwork?

251
00:15:33.963 --> 00:15:35.767
I'll check.

252
00:15:35.869 --> 00:15:37.435
You need to get some sleep.

253
00:15:37.537 --> 00:15:38.832
I'm fine!

254
00:15:39.434 --> 00:15:41.838
He's gonna be gone
in a few months.

255
00:15:41.940 --> 00:15:43.876
Please don't ruin my life!

256
00:15:43.978 --> 00:15:46.310
Priscilla. don't speak to us
like that.

257
00:15:47.775 --> 00:15:50.710
He just lost his mother
and he's still grieving.

258
00:15:51.585 --> 00:15:52.745
He trusts me.

259
00:16:00.122 --> 00:16:01.721
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

260
00:16:03.192 --> 00:16:04.790
(ENGINE REVS. TURNS OFF)

261
00:16:07.930 --> 00:16:09.536
(SIGHS)

262
00:16:09.638 --> 00:16:11.203
(BIRDSONG IN DISTANCE)

263
00:16:13.168 --> 00:16:15.172
(DOOR SQUEAKS OPEN)

264
00:16:15.274 --> 00:16:18.176
- Afternoon. sir.
- How are you. son? C'mon in.

265
00:16:18.278 --> 00:16:19.878
BEAULIEU: That can be tough
this time of year.

266
00:16:19.980 --> 00:16:21.376
ELVIS: No kidding. sir.
We. uh...

267
00:16:21.479 --> 00:16:23.545
We've had some
pretty cold nights out there.

268
00:16:23.647 --> 00:16:25.747
BEAULIEU:
Guess you're looking forward
to getting home?

269
00:16:25.849 --> 00:16:27.749
Yes. sir.

270
00:16:27.851 --> 00:16:29.688
Mmm-hmm.

271
00:16:29.790 --> 00:16:31.751
All right. Here you go.

272
00:16:32.386 --> 00:16:34.620
Well. thank you. ma'am.

273
00:16:34.722 --> 00:16:36.963
Just what is the intent here.
Mr. Presley?

274
00:16:37.065 --> 00:16:38.492
Well. let's face it.
you're Elvis Presley.

275
00:16:38.594 --> 00:16:41.563
You got women
throwing themselves at you.

276
00:16:42.669 --> 00:16:44.236
Why my daughter?

277
00:16:45.702 --> 00:16:48.435
Well. sir. I happen to be
very fond of your daughter.

278
00:16:48.537 --> 00:16:50.736
Uh. she's much more mature
than her age

279
00:16:50.838 --> 00:16:53.641
and I really do enjoy
spending time with her.

280
00:16:53.743 --> 00:16:57.013
I have to admit. you know.
it hasn't been easy for me

281
00:16:57.115 --> 00:16:59.118
being away from home and all.

282
00:16:59.220 --> 00:17:01.420
But you don't have to worry
about her. Captain.

283
00:17:01.523 --> 00:17:03.351
Look. son.

284
00:17:03.453 --> 00:17:05.257
you'll need to
pick her up yourself.

285
00:17:06.219 --> 00:17:07.391
Yes. sir.

286
00:17:07.993 --> 00:17:09.825
Have her home by 2200.

287
00:17:09.927 --> 00:17:11.289
I understand.

288
00:17:11.391 --> 00:17:13.199
BEAULIEU: All right.

289
00:17:30.948 --> 00:17:32.251
Thank you.

290
00:17:34.722 --> 00:17:37.156
- You in?
- Yes.

291
00:17:37.258 --> 00:17:38.817
MAN 1: (ONSCREEN)
<i>Aren't you a teeny bit afraid</i>

292
00:17:38.919 --> 00:17:41.387
<i>that your friend might use it
as an excuse</i>

293
00:17:41.489 --> 00:17:43.392
<i>to begin negotiations elsewhere?</i>

294
00:17:43.495 --> 00:17:46.825
<i>If my friend
were looking for an excuse.</i>

295
00:17:46.927 --> 00:17:48.932
<i>he'd find a better one
in the morning papers.</i>

296
00:17:49.034 --> 00:17:50.400
MAN 1: <i>What do you mean?</i>

297
00:17:50.502 --> 00:17:52.198
MAN 2: <i>I'm talking about
the untimely demise</i>

298
00:17:52.300 --> 00:17:53.602
<i>of Paul Vanmere.</i>

299
00:17:56.444 --> 00:17:58.673
<i>Look. here. Peterson. you don't
have to convince me of anything.</i>

300
00:17:58.775 --> 00:18:00.375
<i>You don't care what I think
as long as I don't</i>

301
00:18:00.477 --> 00:18:02.575
<i>do anything about it.
And I won't.</i>

302
00:18:02.677 --> 00:18:04.280
<i>unless you ever decide
to sic that</i>

303
00:18:04.382 --> 00:18:06.214
<i>knife-happy
little junkie on me.</i>

304
00:18:06.317 --> 00:18:08.085
MAN 1: <i>Watch yourself. laddie.</i>

305
00:18:08.187 --> 00:18:10.487
MAN 3: <i>Now. Jack.
behave yourself.</i>

306
00:18:10.988 --> 00:18:12.555
<i>Sit down.</i>

307
00:18:14.058 --> 00:18:15.658
<i>For shame. Billy.</i>

308
00:18:15.760 --> 00:18:18.964
<i>I think you owe an apology
to everybody in this room.</i>

309
00:18:19.066 --> 00:18:20.861
You ever see
<i>On The Waterfront?</i>

310
00:18:21.397 --> 00:18:24.232
- No.
- Oh. you gotta see it.

311
00:18:24.335 --> 00:18:26.171
There's no one else
like him.

312
00:18:26.273 --> 00:18:29.374
That's the kind of actor
that I wanna be...

313
00:18:30.339 --> 00:18:32.104
I'm sure you will be.

314
00:18:32.874 --> 00:18:36.943
I wanna study at
The Actors Studio in New York.

315
00:18:37.045 --> 00:18:40.649
and tell stories I can really
put myself into. you know?

316
00:18:41.483 --> 00:18:44.224
Like Brando and James Dean.

317
00:18:45.355 --> 00:18:47.019
Well. I think you'd be great.

318
00:18:47.388 --> 00:18:49.328
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

319
00:18:51.827 --> 00:18:53.491
I don't even know
if I'll have a music career

320
00:18:53.593 --> 00:18:55.532
- when I get back.
- What?

321
00:18:56.330 --> 00:18:57.633
Sure you will.

322
00:19:00.834 --> 00:19:03.637
Well. I better go.
it's getting late.

323
00:19:03.739 --> 00:19:05.843
Hold on. they give us these
to stay awake

324
00:19:05.945 --> 00:19:07.544
for night maneuvers.

325
00:19:07.646 --> 00:19:10.481
You can take one in class
if you need to stay awake.

326
00:19:13.952 --> 00:19:15.588
Thank you.

327
00:19:15.690 --> 00:19:17.257
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

328
00:19:22.227 --> 00:19:24.561
- Good night.
- Good night.

329
00:19:25.392 --> 00:19:26.930
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

330
00:19:27.032 --> 00:19:28.598
(ENGINE IDLING)

331
00:19:32.401 --> 00:19:34.099
(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

332
00:19:34.201 --> 00:19:37.376
<i>(FOR SENTIMENTAL REASONS</i>
BY THE RIGHTEOUS BROTHERS
PLAYING)

333
00:19:49.857 --> 00:19:54.019
<i>♪ I love you</i>

334
00:19:55.722 --> 00:20:01.697
<i>♪ For sentimental reasons</i>

335
00:20:03.731 --> 00:20:09.507
<i>♪ I hope you do believe me...</i>

336
00:20:10.976 --> 00:20:12.339
Thank you.

337
00:20:12.441 --> 00:20:18.076
<i>♪ I'll give you my heart</i>

338
00:20:20.282 --> 00:20:21.849
(VOCALIZING)

339
00:20:22.450 --> 00:20:27.459
<i>♪ I love you</i>

340
00:20:28.457 --> 00:20:30.594
<i>♪ And you alone...</i>

341
00:20:30.696 --> 00:20:33.366
I just wish there was some way
I could go with you.

342
00:20:35.268 --> 00:20:37.829
Baby. there's nothing
we can do.

343
00:20:37.931 --> 00:20:43.372
<i>♪ ...your loving heart
To me...♪</i>

344
00:20:43.474 --> 00:20:45.411
I'm just afraid
you'll forget me.

345
00:20:47.543 --> 00:20:49.514
I'm not gonna forget you. Cilla.

346
00:20:50.180 --> 00:20:51.747
Don't you worry.

347
00:21:01.088 --> 00:21:03.229
I know it's not gonna be easy
going back to

348
00:21:03.331 --> 00:21:05.398
being a schoolgirl. Cilla.
but you got to.

349
00:21:06.565 --> 00:21:09.301
Now. I want you to try
to have a good time.

350
00:21:09.403 --> 00:21:11.766
and write me letters
every chance you get.

351
00:21:11.868 --> 00:21:14.407
You get pink stationary
and address them to Joe.

352
00:21:17.373 --> 00:21:18.772
(PRISCILLA SIGHS)

353
00:21:18.875 --> 00:21:21.106
And promise me
you'll stay the way you are now?

354
00:21:24.851 --> 00:21:26.012
I will.

355
00:21:31.355 --> 00:21:32.920
I want you to have this.

356
00:21:39.529 --> 00:21:41.126
All right. baby.
this is it.

357
00:21:42.901 --> 00:21:45.737
Now. don't worry. I'll call you
as soon as I get there.

358
00:21:45.840 --> 00:21:47.833
I promise.

359
00:21:47.935 --> 00:21:49.534
Now. I don't wanna see
a sad face.

360
00:21:49.636 --> 00:21:51.209
(CAR BRAKES SQUEAL)

361
00:21:51.311 --> 00:21:53.446
- (WOMEN CLAMORING)
- (CLEARS THROAT)

362
00:21:56.349 --> 00:21:58.649
(WOMEN SCREAMING
WITH EXCITEMENT)

363
00:22:07.829 --> 00:22:09.429
Bye. baby.

364
00:22:13.064 --> 00:22:15.567
Elvis!

365
00:22:15.669 --> 00:22:18.471
(MELANCHOLY PIANO VERSION
OF <i>LOVE ME TENDER</i> PLAYING)

366
00:22:41.591 --> 00:22:43.826
(INDISTINCT CHATTER. LAUGHTER)

367
00:23:19.392 --> 00:23:22.768
So. the Robinsons invited us
over for dinner next week.

368
00:23:22.870 --> 00:23:24.231
Oh. good.

369
00:23:25.034 --> 00:23:27.705
(PIANO VERSION OF
<i>LOVE ME TENDER</i> CONTINUES)

370
00:24:04.908 --> 00:24:08.142
ANN: Maybe it's time
to forget about him.

371
00:24:08.244 --> 00:24:09.476
Hmm?

372
00:24:09.578 --> 00:24:11.309
I know it's hard.

373
00:24:12.652 --> 00:24:16.017
but he's probably
with women his own age.

374
00:24:16.119 --> 00:24:20.087
What about boys at school?
Must be some handsome ones.

375
00:24:28.002 --> 00:24:29.569
(PHONE RINGS)

376
00:24:32.506 --> 00:24:34.871
- Hello?
- ELVIS: <i>How's my little one?</i>

377
00:24:37.373 --> 00:24:38.743
Elvis?

378
00:24:40.411 --> 00:24:42.340
(PRISCILLA SPUTTERS)

379
00:24:43.380 --> 00:24:44.815
I'm fine...

380
00:24:45.450 --> 00:24:47.015
Only I... I miss you.

381
00:24:48.489 --> 00:24:51.019
I thought you'd
forgotten about me.

382
00:24:51.720 --> 00:24:54.023
My parents said you did.

383
00:24:54.125 --> 00:24:57.355
<i>Oh. baby. things just got
a little crazy being back.</i>

384
00:25:00.193 --> 00:25:02.464
Is it true
about you and Nancy Sinatra?

385
00:25:02.566 --> 00:25:03.931
<i>No. she's a friend.</i>

386
00:25:04.033 --> 00:25:06.299
<i>I'm appearing
on her father's show.</i>

387
00:25:06.401 --> 00:25:10.038
<i>You know. I miss you. baby.
I think about you all the time.</i>

388
00:25:12.180 --> 00:25:14.506
I've missed you so much.

389
00:25:14.608 --> 00:25:17.342
<i>I'd like to make arrangements
for you to visit me in Memphis.</i>

390
00:25:20.548 --> 00:25:21.753
What?

391
00:25:24.223 --> 00:25:25.856
Oh. God. um...

392
00:25:26.858 --> 00:25:29.927
I don't think
my parents will ever let me.

393
00:25:30.363 --> 00:25:32.091
<i>Well. leave that to me.</i>

394
00:25:32.193 --> 00:25:34.700
<i>(HOW YOU SATISFY ME</i>
BY SPECTRUM PLAYING)

395
00:25:50.647 --> 00:25:53.081
<i>♪ Honey. I want you</i>

396
00:25:58.523 --> 00:26:02.959
<i>♪ Honey. I need you</i>

397
00:26:06.259 --> 00:26:10.667
<i>♪ Honey. you know
Just what I need</i>

398
00:26:10.769 --> 00:26:14.399
<i>♪ Come on. take me
Set me free</i>

399
00:26:14.501 --> 00:26:20.306
<i>♪ Well. honey won't you see
How you satisfy me?♪</i>

400
00:26:25.179 --> 00:26:27.515
- (BRAKES SQUEAL)
- (PARKING BRAKE RATCHETS)

401
00:26:27.617 --> 00:26:29.119
(ENGINE TURNS OFF)

402
00:26:29.221 --> 00:26:30.583
Okay.

403
00:26:30.685 --> 00:26:33.019
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

404
00:26:33.121 --> 00:26:34.892
- Come on. honey.
- (CAR DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

405
00:26:46.841 --> 00:26:49.471
- (INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)
- (POOL BALLS CLACKING)

406
00:26:49.573 --> 00:26:51.210
Come on in. honey.

407
00:26:51.312 --> 00:26:53.110
(DODGER LAUGHS WARMLY)

408
00:26:53.913 --> 00:26:56.414
- Here. let me take your things.
- Thank you.

409
00:26:56.516 --> 00:26:58.615
- Well. you made it!
- Yeah.

410
00:26:58.717 --> 00:27:01.046
- Did you have a good trip?
- Yes.

411
00:27:01.148 --> 00:27:03.617
I bet you would like
a lemonade.

412
00:27:03.719 --> 00:27:05.084
(DODGER LAUGHS)

413
00:27:05.186 --> 00:27:07.320
And the boys are just
right down there.

414
00:27:09.227 --> 00:27:10.592
Ooh!

415
00:27:10.694 --> 00:27:13.065
MAN: That's a good shot.

416
00:27:13.167 --> 00:27:14.895
(ALL CHEERING)

417
00:27:14.997 --> 00:27:17.435
ELVIS: I see her.
There she is!

418
00:27:17.537 --> 00:27:19.238
Let me get a good look at you.

419
00:27:19.340 --> 00:27:22.036
Hi. Come on. Mmm-mmm.

420
00:27:22.139 --> 00:27:23.938
Where you been all my life?
Let me see you.

421
00:27:24.040 --> 00:27:25.576
Let me see you.
You look beautiful.

422
00:27:25.678 --> 00:27:27.942
(INHALES)
Oh. you look beautiful.

423
00:27:28.044 --> 00:27:29.574
- Thank you.
- You gotta meet the guys.

424
00:27:29.676 --> 00:27:32.714
This is Hog Ears. You know Joe.
And then the rest of 'em.

425
00:27:32.817 --> 00:27:35.151
- Nice to see you again.
- Hi.

426
00:27:35.520 --> 00:27:37.222
Jerry. A pleasure.

427
00:27:37.324 --> 00:27:38.890
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

428
00:27:40.289 --> 00:27:42.456
O-Five. this here is. uh.
this here is Priscilla.

429
00:27:42.558 --> 00:27:43.959
Hello.

430
00:27:44.061 --> 00:27:46.391
Pleased to meet you. honey.
I'm Alberta.

431
00:27:46.493 --> 00:27:48.293
Nice to meet you.
I've heard so much about you.

432
00:27:48.395 --> 00:27:51.768
And we heard plenty about you.
(CHUCKLES)

433
00:27:51.870 --> 00:27:55.137
Boys. help yourselves.
Dig in. dig in.

434
00:27:55.904 --> 00:27:57.268
Leave some for Priscilla.

435
00:27:57.370 --> 00:27:59.672
- Hi. You hungry?
- It's beautiful here. No.

436
00:27:59.774 --> 00:28:01.374
You like it?

437
00:28:02.909 --> 00:28:04.210
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

438
00:28:04.313 --> 00:28:06.785
I keep trying to tell him
to take me shopping.

439
00:28:06.887 --> 00:28:08.887
- MAN 1: And he won't
take you shopping?
- Well...

440
00:28:08.989 --> 00:28:11.287
MAN 2: No. I take her.
I just... I just stand there.

441
00:28:11.390 --> 00:28:12.990
You tired?

442
00:28:13.524 --> 00:28:15.257
A little bit.

443
00:28:15.359 --> 00:28:16.762
Hmm.

444
00:28:16.864 --> 00:28:19.227
Why don't you go head upstairs?
I'll meet you.

445
00:28:19.329 --> 00:28:21.864
It's just. uh. it's just
the first door on your left.

446
00:28:21.966 --> 00:28:23.533
(SOFT 1960S ROCK MUSIC
PLAYS QUIETLY)

447
00:28:23.635 --> 00:28:25.431
(POOL BALLS CLACKING)

448
00:28:28.442 --> 00:28:30.040
(MAN LAUGHS IN DISTANCE)

449
00:28:32.342 --> 00:28:35.078
JOE: Oh. what up? What up?
MAN: Oh. this is serious.

450
00:28:35.180 --> 00:28:37.849
- Hey. boss. this is Evelyn.
- Evelyn? Who's Evelyn?

451
00:28:37.951 --> 00:28:40.248
- EVELYN: Nice to meet you.
- (JOE AND ELVIS LAUGH)

452
00:28:42.082 --> 00:28:43.889
Wow. she's young. huh?

453
00:28:44.923 --> 00:28:47.723
She's like a little girl.
(CHUCKLING)

454
00:28:47.825 --> 00:28:49.895
(MUSIC AND CHATTER CONTINUES)

455
00:28:59.572 --> 00:29:00.900
(CLOCK TICKS QUIETLY)

456
00:29:01.002 --> 00:29:03.535
(MUSIC THUMPS SLIGHTLY)

457
00:29:13.080 --> 00:29:14.854
(SUITCASE HINGES CREAK)

458
00:29:17.819 --> 00:29:19.584
(FABRIC RUSTLES)

459
00:29:21.592 --> 00:29:23.225
(DOOR OPENS)

460
00:29:23.327 --> 00:29:25.862
ELVIS: Don't let me sleep
no later than 3:00 tomorrow.

461
00:29:25.964 --> 00:29:27.592
- MAN: You got it. boss.
- (DOOR CLOSES)

462
00:29:31.539 --> 00:29:32.968
ELVIS: Where are you. baby?

463
00:29:33.070 --> 00:29:35.600
I'm here.
I'll be just a few minutes.

464
00:29:36.644 --> 00:29:37.936
All right. Don't take too long.

465
00:29:38.038 --> 00:29:39.912
I wanna see my girl.

466
00:29:43.880 --> 00:29:45.918
(GENTLE INHALE. EXHALE)

467
00:29:51.325 --> 00:29:53.156
(DOOR SQUEAKS)

468
00:30:10.140 --> 00:30:12.175
You don't know
how much I missed you.

469
00:30:14.478 --> 00:30:17.180
I haven't been able to get you
out of my head since Germany.

470
00:30:21.548 --> 00:30:23.351
You're the one thing
that kept me going.

471
00:30:41.305 --> 00:30:45.137
Wait. hold on. baby.
things can get out of hand.

472
00:30:45.240 --> 00:30:47.377
What? Is there something wrong?

473
00:30:47.479 --> 00:30:48.973
Just...

474
00:30:49.075 --> 00:30:50.675
Just not yet.

475
00:30:53.213 --> 00:30:54.987
There'll be a right time.

476
00:31:03.194 --> 00:31:05.228
- (PILL BOTTLE CAP POPS)
- (PILLS RATTLE)

477
00:31:06.832 --> 00:31:09.361
Here. you can take one of these.

478
00:31:09.463 --> 00:31:11.531
It'll help you sleep
after your trip.

479
00:31:13.165 --> 00:31:14.770
(LID SNAPS ON)

480
00:31:14.872 --> 00:31:17.075
(BOTTLE TAPS ON TABLE)

481
00:31:23.846 --> 00:31:25.446
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

482
00:31:28.389 --> 00:31:29.516
Come here.

483
00:31:33.460 --> 00:31:35.027
(ELVIS SIGHS)

484
00:31:43.262 --> 00:31:45.004
DODGER: Priscilla?

485
00:31:45.571 --> 00:31:46.764
Priscilla?

486
00:31:47.805 --> 00:31:49.636
Priscilla. hon.

487
00:31:49.971 --> 00:31:52.039
It's Grandma.

488
00:31:52.141 --> 00:31:53.472
What did you give this young'un?

489
00:31:53.574 --> 00:31:55.206
You've got no business
givin' her something

490
00:31:55.308 --> 00:31:56.815
that she's not used to.

491
00:31:56.917 --> 00:31:58.947
You know how long
she's been like this?

492
00:31:59.049 --> 00:32:01.086
You need to call the doctor.

493
00:32:02.184 --> 00:32:04.219
ELVIS: I dunno. she's wakin' up.

494
00:32:04.321 --> 00:32:06.652
- I'll get her some water.
- PRISCILLA: Mmm...

495
00:32:07.859 --> 00:32:10.224
- Where am I?
- Hi. baby.

496
00:32:10.326 --> 00:32:12.328
Baby. we've been
trying to wake you up.

497
00:32:13.193 --> 00:32:14.792
I just went to bed.

498
00:32:15.969 --> 00:32:18.531
No. baby. you've been out
for two days.

499
00:32:18.633 --> 00:32:21.833
On a goddamn 500 milligram
Placidyl. I... I...

500
00:32:21.935 --> 00:32:24.772
I must have been out of my head
givin' it to you that way.

501
00:32:24.874 --> 00:32:26.540
Mmm. mmm...

502
00:32:27.140 --> 00:32:28.509
Mmm. two days?

503
00:32:32.150 --> 00:32:34.383
Well. that's two days
off my trip.

504
00:32:35.716 --> 00:32:37.556
It's fine. you don't
have to worry about it.

505
00:32:37.658 --> 00:32:39.223
We got plenty of time.

506
00:32:40.290 --> 00:32:42.094
So. how'd you
like to go to Vegas?

507
00:32:44.129 --> 00:32:45.926
- Vegas?
- (UPBEAT ROCK AND ROLL SCORE)

508
00:32:46.028 --> 00:32:47.627
(CAR HORNS HONKING)

509
00:32:54.502 --> 00:32:56.273
- (FLASH BULB POPS)
- (PEOPLE CLAMORING)

510
00:33:01.781 --> 00:33:03.346
(EXCITED CONVERSATIONS)

511
00:33:04.850 --> 00:33:07.086
(SLOT MACHINES DINGING)

512
00:33:32.909 --> 00:33:34.542
(CLICKING)

513
00:33:35.307 --> 00:33:36.874
(ALL CHEERING)

514
00:33:39.852 --> 00:33:41.417
(ROULETTE BALL CLACKING)

515
00:33:43.217 --> 00:33:44.783
(GLASSES CLINK)

516
00:33:48.589 --> 00:33:50.894
- (LIQUID SLOSHING)
- (CARDS RIFFLING)

517
00:33:50.997 --> 00:33:53.825
- Twenty-one!
- (ALL CHEERING)

518
00:33:53.927 --> 00:33:57.567
I'm sorry. baby. that's 22.
That's 22. That's a bust.

519
00:33:57.670 --> 00:33:59.033
(LAUGHTER)

520
00:33:59.135 --> 00:34:00.937
- Oh.
- Cilla. baby.

521
00:34:01.039 --> 00:34:03.241
(ELVIS. ENTOURAGE LAUGHING)

522
00:34:13.983 --> 00:34:15.786
(CHEERING)

523
00:34:15.888 --> 00:34:17.522
- Whoo!
- PRISCILLA: Oh!

524
00:34:17.624 --> 00:34:18.919
(ALL LAUGHING)

525
00:34:19.021 --> 00:34:20.858
(WHEEL CLACKING)

526
00:34:20.960 --> 00:34:22.791
MAN: Good for you. young lady.

527
00:34:22.893 --> 00:34:24.493
WOMAN: Whoo!

528
00:34:25.093 --> 00:34:27.430
(TENDER SCORE)

529
00:34:32.033 --> 00:34:33.601
(KISSES)

530
00:34:49.351 --> 00:34:51.652
(MUTED FLASH BULBS POPPING)

531
00:35:12.709 --> 00:35:15.475
ELVIS: Baby. I hate to say it.
but our time is up.

532
00:35:15.577 --> 00:35:18.577
(SNIFFLES)
No. I'm not going back.

533
00:35:18.679 --> 00:35:20.279
I'll call my parents
and tell them

534
00:35:20.381 --> 00:35:21.680
that I missed the flight.

535
00:35:21.782 --> 00:35:23.816
You really think
they're gonna believe that?

536
00:35:24.617 --> 00:35:26.190
Then I'll tell them the truth.

537
00:35:26.292 --> 00:35:27.886
That I love you
and I'm not going back.

538
00:35:27.988 --> 00:35:31.361
Baby. that's just gonna
make it worse for next time.

539
00:35:31.463 --> 00:35:34.231
I gotta go do another film.
so. if you go back

540
00:35:34.333 --> 00:35:35.899
and you do well in school
maybe your parents

541
00:35:36.001 --> 00:35:37.599
will let you come back.

542
00:35:38.804 --> 00:35:40.168
Yes. but when?

543
00:35:40.270 --> 00:35:42.234
We'll sort it out. Come here.

544
00:35:42.336 --> 00:35:43.902
(CRYING SOFTLY)

545
00:35:45.109 --> 00:35:47.004
(AIRPLANE APPROACHING)

546
00:35:54.286 --> 00:35:56.816
(FEMALE PA ANNOUNCER
SPEAKING GERMAN)

547
00:36:01.958 --> 00:36:03.289
What?

548
00:36:03.391 --> 00:36:04.956
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

549
00:36:08.132 --> 00:36:09.697
(SUITCASE HANDLES RATTLE)

550
00:36:25.511 --> 00:36:27.044
(DOOR SLAMMING SHUT)

551
00:36:29.717 --> 00:36:32.390
(CAR DOOR SLAMS SHUT.
ENGINE STARTS)

552
00:36:38.161 --> 00:36:39.991
(GIRLS WHISPERING)

553
00:36:42.561 --> 00:36:44.336
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

554
00:36:48.208 --> 00:36:50.573
(FEMALE TEACHER
SPEAKS FRENCH SLOWLY)

555
00:36:56.112 --> 00:36:57.511
ANN: Why you?

556
00:36:57.613 --> 00:36:59.377
Why can't he find someone
his own age?

557
00:36:59.479 --> 00:37:01.083
You're only 17.

558
00:37:01.185 --> 00:37:03.014
He's not like you imagine.

559
00:37:04.617 --> 00:37:06.923
And he needs me. Mom!

560
00:37:07.025 --> 00:37:09.058
I won't get hurt.

561
00:37:09.160 --> 00:37:11.021
Please. just talk to Dad.

562
00:37:11.123 --> 00:37:13.926
I only have a few more
credits left to graduate.

563
00:37:16.232 --> 00:37:17.798
- Please.
- (SIGHS)

564
00:37:20.599 --> 00:37:22.407
(KISSES) All right.

565
00:37:23.304 --> 00:37:24.876
(SNIFFLES)

566
00:37:24.978 --> 00:37:26.543
Now help me with these.

567
00:37:27.946 --> 00:37:29.579
ELVIS: <i>Sir.</i>

568
00:37:29.681 --> 00:37:31.809
<i>I promise to enroll her
in a good Catholic school</i>

569
00:37:31.911 --> 00:37:34.680
<i>and I'll make sure
she graduates.</i>

570
00:37:34.782 --> 00:37:36.814
<i>She'll live with my father
and Dee</i>

571
00:37:36.916 --> 00:37:38.849
<i>and have a chaperone
at all times.</i>

572
00:37:38.951 --> 00:37:40.488
- Mmm-hmm <i>.
- And my grandmother</i>

573
00:37:40.590 --> 00:37:43.692
<i>and my cousin Patsy
are here. too.</i>

574
00:37:43.794 --> 00:37:46.057
<i>She'll be looked after
as part of the family here.</i>

575
00:37:47.467 --> 00:37:49.531
<i>I love your daughter
and I can assure you</i>

576
00:37:49.633 --> 00:37:52.367
<i>that my intentions
are honorable. sir.</i>

577
00:37:52.469 --> 00:37:53.968
Well. I appreciate
the call. son.

578
00:37:54.070 --> 00:37:55.666
Bye-bye.

579
00:37:55.768 --> 00:37:57.541
(HANDSET CLATTERS INTO CRADLE)

580
00:38:01.042 --> 00:38:02.976
BEAULIEU: (MUFFLED)
She's gotta forget about him.

581
00:38:03.078 --> 00:38:06.349
ANN: And what if she doesn't?
Then she'll never forgive us.

582
00:38:06.451 --> 00:38:08.148
BEAULIEU:
She's gotta finish school.

583
00:38:08.250 --> 00:38:09.553
ANN: I know...

584
00:38:10.518 --> 00:38:12.057
But what are we gonna do?

585
00:38:12.159 --> 00:38:13.622
She said
if we don't let her go.

586
00:38:13.724 --> 00:38:15.789
she's going to find a way
to get there on her own.

587
00:38:15.891 --> 00:38:17.825
BEAULIEU:
She's not gonna get there
on her own.

588
00:38:20.097 --> 00:38:21.832
(TRANQUIL SCORE)

589
00:38:21.934 --> 00:38:23.262
VERNON: Welcome.

590
00:38:23.364 --> 00:38:25.569
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

591
00:38:33.605 --> 00:38:34.976
Oh. Priscilla.

592
00:38:35.078 --> 00:38:37.479
VERNON:
Sorry Elvis's shoot's delayed.
He'll be back soon.

593
00:38:37.581 --> 00:38:39.182
I'll take her
for school registration

594
00:38:39.284 --> 00:38:40.581
just as soon as she's settled.

595
00:38:40.683 --> 00:38:43.116
This girl will be
well looked after.

596
00:38:43.219 --> 00:38:44.786
Thank you.

597
00:38:53.527 --> 00:38:55.093
Please don't worry.

598
00:38:57.530 --> 00:38:58.866
I'll be fine.

599
00:39:11.314 --> 00:39:12.880
(SCORE FADES OUT)

600
00:39:54.754 --> 00:39:56.561
(BIRDS CHIRPING OUTSIDE)

601
00:40:02.463 --> 00:40:04.063
(KEY CLINKS)

602
00:40:11.741 --> 00:40:14.442
Okay. so we'll pick that up
on Friday?

603
00:40:14.545 --> 00:40:16.443
- Oh. hi. Priscilla.
- Hello.

604
00:40:16.545 --> 00:40:18.413
I'm Patsy. this is Becky.

605
00:40:18.515 --> 00:40:20.783
- Hi.
- We run the office here.

606
00:40:20.885 --> 00:40:23.381
It's nice to meet you.
I've heard so much about you.

607
00:40:23.483 --> 00:40:24.950
Us too.

608
00:40:25.052 --> 00:40:27.858
Elvis left a gift for you
on the back patio.

609
00:40:27.960 --> 00:40:29.394
Oh. okay.

610
00:40:29.496 --> 00:40:31.656
You give us a holler
if you need anything.

611
00:40:31.758 --> 00:40:33.623
Okay. thank you. Bye.

612
00:40:33.725 --> 00:40:35.292
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

613
00:40:37.234 --> 00:40:38.900
Hello! (GASPS)

614
00:40:39.368 --> 00:40:41.573
Who are you? Hi.

615
00:40:42.404 --> 00:40:43.971
Hey. little one!

616
00:40:44.472 --> 00:40:46.072
Happy dog.

617
00:40:49.542 --> 00:40:51.110
(KISSES)

618
00:40:52.946 --> 00:40:54.781
ELVIS: (ON PHONE) <i>How's my girl?</i>

619
00:40:54.883 --> 00:40:57.589
I just can't believe
I'm really here.

620
00:40:58.824 --> 00:41:01.323
<i>Yeah. I only have
a little longer on this shoot</i>

621
00:41:01.425 --> 00:41:02.888
<i>and then I'll be home.</i>

622
00:41:02.990 --> 00:41:04.592
<i>Is everyone
taking good care of you?</i>

623
00:41:04.694 --> 00:41:07.997
Yes. Everyone's been
really nice.

624
00:41:08.100 --> 00:41:10.094
<i>- All right. that's good.</i>
- MAN: <i>Elvis.
they're ready for you!</i>

625
00:41:10.196 --> 00:41:12.604
<i>All right. baby.
I gotta get back to set.</i>

626
00:41:13.370 --> 00:41:15.706
Okay. I miss you.

627
00:41:16.538 --> 00:41:18.209
<i>Good night. baby.</i>

628
00:41:18.311 --> 00:41:20.172
- Bye.
- (LINE DISCONNECTS)

629
00:41:21.842 --> 00:41:23.615
(HANDSET CLATTERS INTO CRADLE)

630
00:41:24.679 --> 00:41:26.750
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

631
00:41:29.320 --> 00:41:31.051
(ENGINE TURNS OFF)

632
00:41:34.187 --> 00:41:37.187
- Good luck. have a good day.
- Thank you.

633
00:41:37.290 --> 00:41:39.056
Now. you won't be able
to invite anyone over.

634
00:41:39.158 --> 00:41:40.725
Strangers aren't allowed
in Graceland.

635
00:41:40.827 --> 00:41:42.427
(BELL TOLLING IN DISTANCE)

636
00:41:42.529 --> 00:41:43.767
Okay.

637
00:41:50.176 --> 00:41:51.709
(ENGINE TURNS OVER)

638
00:41:54.241 --> 00:41:57.143
GIRL 1: That's Priscilla.
the girl Elvis is seeing.

639
00:41:59.950 --> 00:42:02.383
NUN: And how does friendship
influence who we are

640
00:42:02.485 --> 00:42:04.449
and what we become?

641
00:42:04.551 --> 00:42:06.886
- Your reports are due Friday.
- GIRL 2: ...with Elvis Presley.

642
00:42:06.988 --> 00:42:08.792
Remember to cite examples
from the text...

643
00:42:08.894 --> 00:42:11.759
If we make friends with her
maybe we can meet him.

644
00:42:11.861 --> 00:42:14.024
And you will be graded
on penmanship

645
00:42:14.126 --> 00:42:16.333
as well as
spelling and grammar.

646
00:42:16.435 --> 00:42:18.065
(EXCITED CHATTER. GIGGLING)

647
00:42:21.437 --> 00:42:22.803
(GENTLE SCORE)

648
00:42:22.905 --> 00:42:25.107
(FANS CONTINUE CHATTERING.
GIGGLING)

649
00:42:25.209 --> 00:42:26.604
(KISSES)

650
00:42:26.706 --> 00:42:28.377
(GENTLE GASP)

651
00:42:28.479 --> 00:42:30.077
(AFFECTIONATE MURMURS)

652
00:42:33.647 --> 00:42:35.051
Oh. honey.

653
00:42:35.153 --> 00:42:38.118
you can't be out here
making a public display
of yourself.

654
00:42:38.753 --> 00:42:40.590
Oh. I didn't think it...

655
00:42:40.692 --> 00:42:42.661
Well. you had
better start thinking.

656
00:42:49.596 --> 00:42:50.834
Come on.

657
00:43:06.582 --> 00:43:08.148
(SCORE FADES OUT)

658
00:43:16.426 --> 00:43:17.993
(MOANS SOFTLY)

659
00:43:20.827 --> 00:43:22.365
(HARP GLISSANDOS)

660
00:43:22.467 --> 00:43:23.832
ANNOUNCER: <i>How elegant!</i>

661
00:43:23.934 --> 00:43:26.865
<i>The most elegant cake
of all: chiffon.</i>

662
00:43:26.967 --> 00:43:28.804
<i>Now dramatically different.</i>

663
00:43:28.906 --> 00:43:31.309
<i>New and deluxe
vanilla cream chiffon</i>

664
00:43:31.411 --> 00:43:33.371
<i>with an exotic new taste!</i>

665
00:43:33.473 --> 00:43:37.947
<i>It's vanilla. cream
and a French flavor secret.</i>

666
00:43:38.514 --> 00:43:40.685
<i>Tantalizing.</i>

667
00:43:40.787 --> 00:43:42.147
ELVIS: (ON PHONE) <i>I said
to the director today.</i>

668
00:43:42.250 --> 00:43:44.388
<i>"Why'd we come all the way
to Los Angeles</i>

669
00:43:44.491 --> 00:43:45.690
<i>"to film the Smoky Mountains?</i>

670
00:43:45.792 --> 00:43:47.188
<i>"Hell. you may know more
about movie makin'.</i>

671
00:43:47.290 --> 00:43:49.326
<i>"but I know a thing or two
about the Smoky Mountains.</i>

672
00:43:49.428 --> 00:43:50.287
<i>"And I'll tell you what.</i>

673
00:43:50.390 --> 00:43:52.456
<i>"they ain't got no
coconut trees on 'em!"</i>

674
00:43:54.795 --> 00:43:56.398
<i>You there. baby?</i>

675
00:43:56.500 --> 00:43:58.099
Mmm-hmm. I'm here.

676
00:43:59.030 --> 00:44:00.299
<i>How're you doin'?</i>

677
00:44:01.273 --> 00:44:02.835
I'm great.

678
00:44:02.938 --> 00:44:05.376
It's all been really wonderful.

679
00:44:05.478 --> 00:44:07.172
<i>That's what I like to hear.</i>

680
00:44:07.274 --> 00:44:09.276
<i>Baby. do you have
everything you need?</i>

681
00:44:09.745 --> 00:44:11.376
<i>How you doin' on cash?</i>

682
00:44:12.385 --> 00:44:14.484
It's funny you should ask.

683
00:44:14.586 --> 00:44:16.485
Your daddy's pretty strict.

684
00:44:16.587 --> 00:44:17.920
(ELVIS LAUGHS QUIETLY)

685
00:44:18.022 --> 00:44:20.792
<i>Yeah. that's my daddy.
He's always been tight.</i>

686
00:44:20.894 --> 00:44:23.119
<i>That's why I have him
taking care of the bills.</i>

687
00:44:23.221 --> 00:44:25.663
<i>I don't trust anybody else.</i>

688
00:44:25.766 --> 00:44:27.965
<i>Don't worry about it.
I'll talk to him.</i>

689
00:44:28.067 --> 00:44:31.166
There's a boutique that said
I could work there part-time.

690
00:44:31.268 --> 00:44:34.168
I thought I could work there
a few days a week after school.

691
00:44:36.809 --> 00:44:38.403
<i>Well. you'll have to
forget about that.</i>

692
00:44:39.544 --> 00:44:41.109
I thought it could be fun.

693
00:44:43.343 --> 00:44:45.178
<i>Well. it's either me
or a career. baby.</i>

694
00:44:45.280 --> 00:44:47.819
<i>When I call you.
I need you to be there for me.</i>

695
00:44:49.452 --> 00:44:50.688
Mmm-hmm.

696
00:44:50.790 --> 00:44:52.791
<i>Just a few more days
and we'll be home.</i>

697
00:44:54.556 --> 00:44:55.860
Okay.

698
00:44:56.922 --> 00:44:59.394
I love you. Bye.

699
00:44:59.496 --> 00:45:00.898
<i>Bye. baby.</i>

700
00:45:02.062 --> 00:45:04.261
(HANDSET CLATTERS INTO CRADLE)

701
00:45:04.363 --> 00:45:05.930
- (GATE UNLOCKING)
- (CAR HORN HONKING)

702
00:45:06.032 --> 00:45:07.806
(FANS YELLING EXCITEDLY)

703
00:45:10.773 --> 00:45:13.270
Memphis. we're back. baby!

704
00:45:13.372 --> 00:45:16.212
It's good to be home!
Where's my Cilla?

705
00:45:16.314 --> 00:45:17.709
Hello.

706
00:45:17.811 --> 00:45:19.746
Hello. Hello.

707
00:45:19.848 --> 00:45:21.446
(ANIMATED CONVERSATIONS)

708
00:45:24.716 --> 00:45:26.885
Dodger. you waited for me too.
Bless your little heart.

709
00:45:26.987 --> 00:45:28.826
I did. Welcome home. baby.

710
00:45:28.928 --> 00:45:30.987
Good to see you. baby.
O-Five. what's for dinner?

711
00:45:31.089 --> 00:45:32.824
(BAND MUSIC PLAYS)

712
00:45:32.926 --> 00:45:34.327
Cilla. come here.

713
00:45:35.961 --> 00:45:37.297
How's school?

714
00:45:37.963 --> 00:45:39.364
Oh. it's okay.

715
00:45:39.466 --> 00:45:42.133
- I don't really talk
to anybody there.
- Hmm.

716
00:45:42.235 --> 00:45:44.238
Grandma and Patsy
have been nice.

717
00:45:44.772 --> 00:45:46.372
I missed you.

718
00:45:47.507 --> 00:45:49.680
I've been trying to
find things to do with my...

719
00:45:49.782 --> 00:45:51.408
You gotta keep up
with your schoolwork

720
00:45:51.510 --> 00:45:53.478
otherwise your father
won't let you stay.

721
00:45:54.821 --> 00:45:57.482
- I know. but...
- You sure do look pretty.

722
00:45:58.416 --> 00:46:00.188
C'mon. let's have
something to eat.

723
00:46:03.092 --> 00:46:04.791
O-Five. I sure did
miss you. baby!

724
00:46:04.893 --> 00:46:06.461
Let me see you. (KISSES)

725
00:46:06.563 --> 00:46:07.859
Hand me a plate.

726
00:46:07.961 --> 00:46:09.395
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

727
00:46:09.497 --> 00:46:11.669
MAN: I'll tell you.
that Ursula was always around.

728
00:46:11.771 --> 00:46:13.899
Oh. goddamn man.
she was a big woman.

729
00:46:14.001 --> 00:46:15.465
- (MAN LAUGHS)
- She was.

730
00:46:15.567 --> 00:46:18.170
- Was she pretty?
- She had a body like a man.

731
00:46:18.272 --> 00:46:19.911
No hips.
